Class SearchInformation

    • Method Detail

      • getPvNumber

        public abstract int getPvNumber()
        Returns the index of the PV line. If multi-PV is not supported, it should always return 0. If it is supported, the numbering should start from 1 with the best line.
        Returns:
        The index of the PV line.

      • getPv

        public abstract String[] getPv()
        Returns an array of the principal variation with the moves in Pure Algebraic Coordinate Notation.
        Returns:
        An array of the moves in PACN that make up the PV.

      • getCurrentMove

        public abstract String getCurrentMove()
        Returns the currently searched root move in Pure Algebraic Coordinate Notation. If it returns null, it is ignored.
        Returns:
        The currently search root move in PACN.

      • getCurrentMoveNumber

        public abstract int getCurrentMoveNumber()
        Returns the number of the currently searched move in the move list of the root position. If it returns 0, it is ignored.
        Returns:
        The current move index in the list of legal moves.

      • getDepth

        public abstract short getDepth()
        Returns the nominal depth of the search.
        Returns:
        The nominal depth of the search.

      • getSelectiveDepth

        public abstract short getSelectiveDepth()
        Returns the greatest depth of the search.
        Returns:
        The greatest depth of the search.

      • getScore

        public abstract short getScore()
        Returns the result score of the search for the side to move.
        Returns:
        The search score in centipawns or if it is a mate score, the mate distance.

      • getScoreType

        public abstract ScoreType getScoreType()
        Returns whether it is an exact score, a lower bound, an upper bound, or a mate score, in which case the score denotes the mate distance in half moves. If the side to move in the root position is going to get mated, the negative distance is returned.
        Returns:
        The type of the returned score.

      • getNodes

        public abstract long getNodes()
        Returns the number of nodes searched to reach this result.
        Returns:
        The number of nodes traversed.

      • getTime

        public abstract long getTime()
        Returns the time spent on the search to reach this result in milliseconds.
        Returns:
        The time spent searching in milliseconds.

      • getEndgameTablebaseHits

        public abstract long getEndgameTablebaseHits()
        Returns the number of endgame tablebase hits while searching.
        Returns:
        The number of endgame tablebase hits.

      • getCurrentLine

        public abstract int getCurrentLine()
        Returns the number of the line the engine is currently calculating. In concurrent engines, this may be the thread/process number. It should start 1. If it is 0 or less, it is ignored.
        Returns:
        The current line number.

      • getString

        public abstract String getString()
        Returns any additional information the engine wants to send. If it is null, it is ignored.
        Returns:
        Any additional information.
